```js
<ViewTransition
  onEnter={(instance) => {
    const anim = instance.new.animate(/* ... */);
    return () => {
      anim.cancel();
    };
  }}
  onExit={(instance) => {
    const anim = instance.new.animate(/* ... */);
    return () => {
      anim.cancel();
    };
  }}
>
  {/* ... */}    
</ViewTransition>
```

If you have a pending`onEnter` animation and the tree is unmounted, the `onEnter` cleanup is called immediately.

But if you have a pending `onExit` and the tree is unmounted, the `onExit` cleanup isn't called until the animation completes.

This means you can't cancel the animation:

